<br>
What right have you to send the false League to my city to question me??  <br>
<br>
So that you know, I always saw through your feeble attempt at disguise, and have known Fauntley was a fake name.<br>
<br>
You are enemy Sergian, I thought you could be used, but you are more trouble than you are worth.<br>
<br>
Luckily, you are also more trouble than it is worth my while to kill.  However, I plan on acquiring Gerard for my own servant. I tell you this only because of the scorn in which I hold your powers.   <p><img border=0 src="http://www.leagueofshadows.net/sigs/Littany.jpg" /></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=littanydthule>LittanyDThule</A> at: 6/24/03 10:30 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=melediweaver>melediweaver</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Dirges, a specialty</span><br>  Posts: 339<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(6/24/03 11:00 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=924.topic&index=22>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A letter to my esteemed colleague, Flamerge Flindin-Klap</span><hr size=1> Dear Sergian,<br>
<br>
On your behalf, the League ventured a few days ago into Paineel.  To our surprise, our way was barred by Dreyk, a beastlord of much power, and the priestess Littany stood with him. They delayed us long enough that others of the foul League of Shadows were able to gather, Khurai, Slob, Kyri, Adar and the ilk. <br>
<br>
Dreyk defeated me in combat, as he did Rrome, and Walkingwolf, Kerys, and some others of my clan and extended family. Artanis fell to Kyri, Khurai defeated Flamerge and Adanus, but I will admit, without Dreyk it would have been much easier. At last Dreyk fell to the mighty hammer of Blayze, and we were able to enter into the city. Not uncontested mind you, the Shadows massed behind us, and it was only after we stained the floor of the arena with their blood that Paineel was ours. It was with great satisfaction that we took down first Adar, then Dreyk, then Slob in the battle royale. Aoleus of course was more than happy to provide the cleansing fire we wielded in this city.<br>
<br>
The priestess Littany was defeated, both by Zippus, a young wizard who will join us, and by Raires, a paladin of our ranks. However, she managed to slink off and evade the questions I would have asked her.<br>
<br>
Need I emphasize however that she has more than demonstrated she is not a safe, or desirable companion?<br>
<br>
Meledi Weaver<br>
Bard of 58 songs<br>
League of Honour<br>
 <p><img border=0 src="http://home.golden.net/~effinger/sig.jpg" /></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=melediweaver>melediweaver</A> at: 6/24/03 2:53 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=sergianfv>SergianFV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(6/24/03 7:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=924.topic&index=23>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A letter to my esteemed colleague, Flamerge Flindin-Klap</span><hr size=1> * in a rather scrawled script*<br>
