Deer Preest Gurl frum Payneel!<br>
<br>
Der no majishin heer jus sum stoopid Troll (dats me!)!  Dat dum majishin is gon an him went sumweres rilly rilly far away an him dint leev no forwurdin adress!  So me gess yu not haf tu come heer tu bash nobuddy ok?  Me tink him gon tu da moon or sumptin so yu go dere now ok?  RAMEMBUR!  Yu duzzint haf tu come heer!  Yu go tu da MOON!!<br>
<br>
BYBY!<br>
<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=sergianfv>SergianFV</A> at: 6/24/03 9:05 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=sergianfv>SergianFV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(6/24/03 8:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=924.topic&index=24>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A letter to my esteemed colleague, Flamerge Flindin-Klap</span><hr size=1> Bard:<br>
<br>
Egads, woman, what have you done?  In &quot;my name,&quot; you may have singlehandedly reignited hostilities between grand Erudin and that festering cesspool, Paineel.  In addition, it seems you have unhinged the frail sanity of this priestess, Littany, who now blames me singularly for her dismal existence.  She now suffers from apparently murderous intent.  Can you venture a supposition as to whom this intent shall be directed?<br>
<br>
To buy time, I have misled the Priestess, sending her on a fool's errand to Luclin.  But I should think that, in her fleeting lucidity, she may still possess the faculty to discover this ruse.  She is, after all, Erudite.  Therefore, while I can, I shall travel eastward in heavy disguise and under pseudonym.  I shall also be making use of one of my other companions, Wembley.  Gerard I have dispatched to the Plane of Earth as he has now become a liability.<br>
<br>
I have arranged quarters for myself in Freeport a...how shall I say it...a &quot;safe house.&quot;  The details of said arrangement I shall not reveal at present.  Suffice to say that I shall address you in that dilapidated excuse for a city so that we may discuss means of restitution for this dilemma.<br>
<br>
Good day,<br>
<br>
Sergian Singian-Smythe, Esq.<br>
<br>
